ients": ["2 large rump steaks (about 240g each)", "50g cornflour", "4 tbsp vegetable oil", "45g chopped chilli, ginger and garlic paste", "3 tbsp hoisin sauce", "4 tbsp white wine vinegar", "2 large oranges, zested and juiced", "3 tbsp sweet chilli sauce", "2 tbsp dark soy sauce", "1/2 bunch spring onions, finely chopped", "1 red chilli, finely sliced", "cooked rice to serve", "steamed pak choi to serve"], "act_instructions": "Cut the beef into thin strips, pat dry with kitchen paper then toss in the cornflour, and set aside.\nHeat 1 tbsp vegetable oil in a large non-stick frying pan over a high heat, fry the chopped chilli, garlic and ginger paste for 1-2 mins, not letting the garlic burn, then add the hoisin, white wine vinegar, zest and juice of the oranges, sweet chilli sauce and soy sauce.\nBring the boil and then simmer for around 5 mins until you have a thick, sticky sauce and have reduced the liquid volume by half. Remove to a bowl.\nHeat a clean large non stick frying pan or wok until very hot, then add 3 tbsp of vegetable oil, before adding the steak to stir fry for a few minutes until it takes on colour.\nPour in the sauce, toss together and cook for another couple of minutes until the sauce is sticking to the beef. Garnish with chopped spring onions and extra chilli. Great served with pak choi and fluffy rice.", "act_image": "https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2021/01/Crispy-beef-in-chilli-sauce-1cc40ba.jpg", "act_nutrients": {"calories": "421 calories", "fatContent": "23 grams fat", "saturatedFatContent": "5 grams saturated fat", "carbohydrateContent": "26 grams carbohydrates", "sugarContent": "12 grams sugar", "fiberContent": "2 grams fiber", "proteinContent": "27 grams protein", "sodiumContent": "2.03 milligram of sodium"}}